  <refnamediv>
    <refname>polyphase_filter</refname>
    <refpurpose>Creation of a polyphase decimation filter structure</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   H = polyphase_filter(h,m)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>h:</term>
      <listitem><para> FIR filter coefficients (1d vector)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>m:</term>
      <listitem><para> number of polyphase branches e.g. decimation ratio</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>H:</term>
      <listitem><para> resulting polyphase matrix form</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
Creation of the polyphase matrix. The filter is decomposed into m
phases sub-filters (m rows of the H matrix). Each sub-filter can
process a decimated version of the input signal, with a different phase.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

